<br>
First off, I would like to start by saying I have seen this before on some website's message board, but after hours of looking I can't seem to find it.<br>
<br>
So, I came here. =)<br>
<br>
Anyway, I was wondering if anyone can tell me any armor that would turn me away from that dreaded n00b potato sack looking armor :).  <br>
<br>
I wanna really stand out in my armor/weapons, but right now, I only have the following &quot;stand out-ish&quot; armor/weaps:<br>
<br>
Melee: Velium Etched Stone Mace &amp; Testament (Staple of almost every 20+ druid, but I still love the look, nonetheless)<br>
<br>
Wrists: Runed Minthril Bracer's<br>
<br>
Arms: Bone Armplate<br>
<br>
That's about it.  The rest is either leather or tizmak, i.e. potato sack armor. Hehe.<br>
<br>
So, if anyone could tell me anything better to upgrade my other slots with, I would be greatly appreciative.<br>
<br>
--Just a few last notes:<br>
  1.  I would prefer if the item gave wisdom too, as I am not at the stage yet where I can have a few high wisdom items to compensate for cool looking non-wis items.<br>
  2.  I hate the look of any caster helm at all, so runed circlet is outta the question.<br>
  3.  I have about 1.5k to spend, but once I hit 29 I expect to get quite a bit more from TP's.<br>
<br>
Thanks All! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoooga99.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oooga99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 7:50:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /bump</span><hr size=1> /bump<br>
<br>
Please respond :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 10:50:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bump</span><hr size=1> Well...not sure what peices of crystal chiten give wis, but it has a cool silverish look to it. Depends on what race you are...but IMHO Ulthork looks pimp on halflings :). ES stuff gives a cool green look (probably too expensive...and it doesn't give wis unless u get the top 2 pieces :) bp n legs) he he he. Well, hope this helps.<br>
<br>
Fyrrwin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaraethonii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karaethon II</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 11:08:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bump</span><hr size=1> He said he's below 29...with 1.5k. So think CC and ES a little out. Try Gnome Skin. You'll have to buy it. and more and more druids are starting to wear it..but it looks great. No wis component except for the gloves though<br>
<br>
-Karaethon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 12:03:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bump</span><hr size=1> He he he, that is why I said that it was probably too expensive...was just listing some of the armors :)<br>
<br>
Fyrrwin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoooga99.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oooga99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 2:57:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Armor: FYI</span><hr size=1> I also have a 38 necro too, btw.  <br>
<br>
So would any CC or ES stuff be in my range if I hunted in any of those places and won the rolls?  Just a thought I might add.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoooga99.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oooga99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 3:00:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Arm Slot</span><hr size=1> Sorry I didn't put it in the above post, but I just camped last night (REAL easy camp) platinum armbands for my druid.<br>
<br>
I found out it doesn't have any graphic at all.  It has way better stats than leather, but unless people inspect me, it looks like I don't even have any arm's on.<br>
<br>
Anyone know of any arms that give wis that DO have a graphic? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 3:15:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Arm Slot</span><hr size=1> Like I said...ulthork looks pretty spiffy. You won't have a chance on ES or CC for several more lvls, since CC drops in Velktor (sp?) and ES drops in Kanor/Seb...*shrug*<br>
<br>
Fyrrwin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoooga99.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oooga99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 12:43:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ulthork</span><hr size=1> Hey Fyrrwin,<br>
<br>
Can you tell me what Ulthork looks like?  I've probably seen it but haven't had the time to inspect. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 1:20:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ulthork</span><hr size=1> What racer are you? On humans it looks kinda orangish...halflings is a dark purple with silverish lines...woodelf...hard to describe, is brown with green and other colored lines. Don't know on half elfs...Looks best on halflings IMHO, maybe I am biased a bit :).<br>
<br>
Fyrrwin <br>
40th halfling druid of Bertoxx :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoooga99.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oooga99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 3:15:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Woody Here</span><hr size=1> Woody Druid here =)<br>
<br>
I saw some pics on Fashion Tables on allakhazam, and it looks.....um...different.<br>
<br>
I was also checking the stats of it, and frankly, I really don't like having too many negative stats.  <br>
<br>
Almost every piece of Ulthork has a negative statistic to it too.<br>
<br>
Anyway, thanks for recommending anything.  But does anyone have any idea of what kinda armor looks cool also?  My friend suggested a Black Chitin Leggings/Brown Chitin Protector Combo, but I can't afford the leg slot if I can stash Gatorscale there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufyrrwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fyrrwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 3:28:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Woody Here</span><hr size=1> Well...that is a GREAT looking combo on a wood elf...not great stats though...gator legs are sooooo much better...but BCL look better *shrug*<br>
<br>
Fyrrwin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upinepath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pinepath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/30/01 5:38:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Elf druid armor.</span><hr size=1> Now that they took the blue diamond requirement off of the smithed elven cultural armor, enchanted/imbued elven chain is once again a viable druid armor.  You might camp Mistmoore and Najena/steamfont for the temper components, which are the only real factor in the rarity of this.  And of course the rarity of high elven smiths.  Not on MM are you?  Heh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3167.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3162.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=3155.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=3155.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3155.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3155.topic>Unsubscribe</